##Online education, traffic, how to catch?

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

By Yana Meng

Editor | Zhou Changfan

More than 600,000 teachers in more than 300 cities have become anchors as public schools across the country began offering classes online on Feb. 10. First contact online teaching, part of the teachers at a loss, become the protagonist of the network joke, chaos like sentient beings.

In response to the school suspension policy, several head online education institutions have donated free public welfare courses to primary and secondary school students across the country. At the same time, there is no smoke flow contention also quietly broke out.

And this epidemic, the impact of the larger offline training institutions, then choose to close the store wait and see or emergency courses moved to the line, pray to survive the difficulties. Some educational institutions, due to aggressive expansion, cash flow disruption, unfortunately died, the old IT training institutions announced the bankruptcy of brothers, Ming big language capital chain broken business.

In the secondary market, a large influx of traffic, the demand for online education surge, so that online education by the capital of the favor. A shares opened a few days ago, online education stocks for several consecutive days trading limit, in the US and Hong Kong stock markets, New Oriental Online, good future, learn from WHO, Netease Youdao and other online education concepts stock rally is also very fierce.

This epidemic has raised the awareness of online education, and at the same time, it has accelerated the speed of online education.

Under the peak of flow

Infrastructure and faculty expansion

Since Jan. 22, the number of ClassIn back end sign ups for online classroom streaming systems for educational institutions has skyrocketed, reaching a peak of more than 1.6 million students a day and more than 350,000 online. Compared with the usual peak learning period, the number of users suddenly increased by nearly 10 times.

"At first our best option was to expand to 3-5 times capacity, but as the number of users grew, it expanded to 10 times, then to 30 times, and now it's in the millions, " ClassIn co-founder Taniwa told comscore.

Like ClassIn, on the first day of primary and secondary school, almost all of the service platforms that hosted online classes had problems with large areas of Cottonwood and delays. On the first day of the class, the platform flooded 5 million users, causing Internet congestion and a rush in Cottonwood, the team said. The Spike, tencent and other apps that provide platforms for educational institutions have also gone Cottonwood and crashed. In the face of a short-term surge in the number of students, the platform has been an emergency expansion.

Generally speaking, the platform will not blindly expand capacity, Guyan explained to CNNMONEY. The technology reserve needs to be done well in advance to help the platform achieve higher goals. In addition to bandwidth issues, the platform also needs to have a stable underlying software architecture and physical resource server support. On the one hand, during this period, bandwidth resources are relatively tight, in addition to online education platform, some conference video software platform also need a lot of bandwidth. On the other hand, during the Spring Festival, business is basically in a semi-paralyzed state, some physical resources are more difficult to buy in a short time.

CLASSIN's network stability was put to the test early in the winter break. As a rule, the platform's online resources, cloud servers, bandwidth and so on all need to go through about two weeks of debugging before it comes online, but this time is completely "while flying the plane while repairing the engine" state.

"A lot of people joke that we belong to the epidemic unit, and what you see is that our user numbers are going up, but we're also very invested in doing this. "Taniyan said. Classin hadn't had a chance to do the math, and when he decided to expand, he didn't have time to do it.

Some of the head of the platform for the emergency investment are over ten million yuan level. Li Xin, vice president of Simian Guidance, said in a recent interview that the cost of bandwidth will exceed 100 million this month because of the free live streaming course. He has already sold out all the resources available on the market. If the data continues to rise, i'M GONNA have to go to the employee relations department.

After the infrastructure problem of the platform is solved, the teacher strength is highlighted again, and becomes a big problem.

The influx of users in a short period of time has put pressure on the platform's teaching staff, several online education institutions told CNNMONEY. In the last month, almost all of the teachers have been 007. K12, a K12 online education platform, recently partnered with Xiaoshan District primary and secondary schools in Hangzhou to provide a full range of services including platform, teachers and content. "This donation campaign has brought 100,000 users to 100 percent of the class in a short period of time, which has reached the limit of the pressure on the platform, and is also a test for teachers to teach, " Coo Wang Yanfei told CNFC.

Offline institutions, by contrast, have had a tougher time, with teachers who have never been exposed to online instruction turning into anchors, causing all sorts of discomfort. Lack of live broadcast equipment, made a simple version of the mobile phone rack with a coat hanger; not familiar with the live broadcast software, will beauty to the maximum function, but also in the middle of the live broadcast was interrupted by family collapse; network platform crowded, the teacher did not squeeze in; forgot to open the microphone the whole time, mute finished a class completely ignorant, recently the network class large-scale rollover spot frequency hot search.

In terms of form, most of the courses donated by K12 online education companies are online large class live courses, and there is no obvious difference, and large class live courses are also recognized as a higher risk-resistant model in the industry, because you can take advantage of the large class live streaming class without borders, while covering more users. In the view of the founder of love to learn, most parents would recognize the famous teacher effect, but very few good teachers.

But on the other hand, compared with small class and 1V1 teaching, large class is very test of the ability of teachers to control the field, as well as to cope with the different levels of users of the strain. Therefore, excellent teachers are still the core competitiveness of each organization to attract users.

Pexels

In the field of online education, K12 subject counseling is a complicated market. Because there are great differences in textbook version, difficulty, progress and test type in different areas of the country, and these differences also lead to K12 subject products can not be developed by one standard system.

In order to solve this problem, most institutions have adopted the method of teaching material layering, which is distinguished when students register, such as Beijing Normal University edition, People's Education Edition, Shanghai Education Edition, etc. . Luo Yuan, vice president of Netease Youdao, told the Financial Times that as the user group from first-and second-tier cities to cover the country, Netease Youdao has adopted a hierarchical teaching model and regional management of tutors. With the influx of more users from different regions, the demand for teachers has also increased rapidly.

The free live lesson appears to have brought a significant number of users to online educational institutions, but unlike pure internet products, parents and students often choose an educational product based on quality and word of mouth. Therefore, free classes for most online education institutions, more is just a public good, the actual student attendance rate is not high.

"For online education, in the end, it's all about content and word of mouth. No matter how hot the so-called online education is now, you have to master the content, " Luo said.

Free classes are not as popular as low-priced ones

In the face of the epidemic, most educational institutions have contributed by donating free classes and money and materials. Learn and think net school, New Oriental, learn from WHO, love to learn, ape counseling and other institutions have launched free public interest live lessons.

Recently, in the Netease Youdao Open class of the B Station Learning Festival, a chemistry teacher took apart two of his son's toys and showed his students how to make 84 disinfectant solution. A geography teacher held up a basin and talked about topographic maps, another biology teacher, dressed as a bat, vividly tells the virus 10,086 kinds of careful machine... in order to arouse students'interest in class, these teachers, sometimes serious and sometimes lively, painstakingly.

From the view of curriculum design, different institutions try to attract the attention of users with different curriculum methods. A quality class in the B station to open a live customized course content; learning and think school invited Lang Lang to do open classes; The guide invited Ji Lianhai, host of Lecture Hall, Kang Zhen, Professor of Beijing Normal University, Liu Yong and other famous writers to open the Public Welfare Lecture Hall.

But no matter what content is offered, the K12 course is undoubtedly the one most in demand.

By giving away free public courses, institutions have solved the problem of online learning for students across the country and further built awareness of online education among students and parents. For some parents who have not been exposed to online education, suspension facilitates their participation in online education, but for users who already have a need for online education, said Chen Xiangdong, founder of WHO, free classes are not as popular as low-priced ones.

The free course is a special period benefit for children, the difference from the spring course is the lack of targeted tutoring and services, according to Kol. COM, homework help, and monkey guidance. Low-cost courses, by contrast, are experiential courses that condense courses and services into a single package, usually the first few sessions of a course.

Luo told CNBC that free classes are an important part of the process for parents to build their awareness of online education from 0 to 1. A user usually really from know to use, need to go through many steps, from know to purchase, there still need to be a large span, and free lessons can be low threshold to build parents'trust, quality is good, parents can make their own judgment about whether to continue to buy more classes and services through free experiential classes.

Chen did the math on Feb. 19 during the Q4 earnings call for the 2019 fiscal year.

There are about 200 million primary and secondary school students in China. Suppose the cost of running a primary and secondary school student from offline to online is about 1,000 yuan, multiplied by the total cost is 200 billion yuan. There are nearly 20 million teachers from primary and secondary schools and after school programs. If the cost of training a teacher online is 200 yuan, the total cost is 40 billion yuan. In short, the outbreak has saved the online education industry nearly 240 billion yuan in promotional costs.

The platform attracted nearly 15 million registered users during the free lessons, the earnings call also revealed. However, Chen Xiangdong says that the number of users is not equal to the number of customers, although attracting customers can be quick, but it takes longer to accumulate loyal customers. A user signs up for three free real time classes, he says, and then decides whether to take a low cost promotion course or not. Since this process is one step more than switching directly from the RMB9 real-time course, the conversion rate is certainly much lower.

In addition, for users, because learning is irreversible, trial and error costs are relatively high, most students will not choose too much time to try a different platform. During the winter vacation, netease has a way through user research, found that most of the junior high school students winter vacation has been the school layout full of tasks, their time is not very abundant. In contrast, low-cost paid classes are more acceptable to parents, users in the unit time for low-cost Class Satisfaction is very high. The core reason, Luo says, is that what parents and students really need is short, effective courses, which condense the essence of the course per unit of time so that the user experience is better.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In fact, online education is no stranger to offline organizations and users. China's online education market is expected to reach 313.36 billion yuan in 2019, up 24.5 percent year on year, and users'acceptance of online education is on the rise, according to Iresearch, the main reasons for the continuous growth of the online education market are the gradual development of online payment consciousness and the improvement of online learning experience and effect.

But there is no denying that this outbreak has greatly enhanced the penetration of online education, the suspension of classes without suspension policy, students from all over the country into the online platform, the sinking market layer was easily broken. In the past, each online education institutions will choose to deal with first-and second-tier cities, and then sink market breakthrough. During this outbreak, the sunken market was unexpectedly opened.

Taniyan observed that some of the offline transformation of institutions, much faster than expected. She found that on the ClassIn platform, teachers from offline institutions were able to apply the platform's tools surprisingly quickly. In class, teachers and students on the platform of the blackboard synchronous writing communication, learning more efficient. The outbreak has spurred a push by offline education institutions to experiment with online instruction, accelerating the convergence of online and offline instruction.

But at this stage, offline training institutions are still among the most vulnerable. Not only do they face rent pressures, but teachers and students have difficulty attending classes, teachers are not being recruited and trained at the same pace, and online education giants are offering free courses, for the offline body is also a kind of impact.

In Luo's view, the epidemic is a double-edged sword to the development of online education. People will find some shortcomings while experiencing online courses, such as the rollover of online courses. This will also help expose the shortcomings more thoroughly and make parents'choices more rational. For some companies that focus on content and services, it is possible to become a development node.

Taniyan also believes that from the sub-epidemic is the next two to three years of online education development preview. In the wake of the epidemic, what is left for third party education platform institutions is the number of new users, while what is left for institutions is the recognition of the online education model, where opportunities and challenges for all exist side by side.

"In the past, most of the parents in the entire education market were relatively new to child discipline, and only 20 percent of the parents were willing to take the initiative to try online education, but I predict that the proportion will rise to 50 percent in the coming years, " Zeng Pengxuan, the founder of walnut programming, told CAIJING, in the short term, it's not going to be very good for online education, but it's going to have a long term effect as customers and markets are educated.

Xu Jicheng, the founder of love to learn, believes that the current stage only speeds up the integration of offline education and online education. "Just as the rise of e-commerce after SARS did not completely replace offline consumption, neither did education. "
